item.title: CVE-2022-26376|2024-09-16T22:01:42.801Z -- asuswrt-merlin -- asuswrt-merlin%20new%20gen
item.description: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in the httpd unescape functionality of Asuswrt prior to 3.0.0.4.386_48706 and Asuswrt-Merlin New Gen prior to 386.7.. A specially-crafted HTTP request can lead to memory corruption. An attacker can send a network request to trigger this vulnerability.
